
[1]confiscate

   CONFISCATE, v.t. [L., a basket, hamper or bag; hence, revenue or the
   Emperors treasure.] To adjudge to be forfeited to the public treasury,
   as the goods or estate of a traitor or other criminal, by way of
   penalty; or to condemn private forfeited property to public use.

   The estate of the rebels was seized and confiscated.

    CONFISCATE, a. Forfeited and adjudged to the public treasury, as the
                            goods of a criminal.
